website_summaries.verdict: If you’re hunting for a raw and grain-free diet, you can’t go wrong with one of the protein-loaded kibble recipes from Instinct.
pros: Rabbit, turkey, and fish are the first 3 ingredients
The recipe is 80% animal proteins and 20% wholesome ingredients like peas and cranberries
cons: The raw diet isn’t for every cat

customer_reviews.title: Beware: they are now adding Medadione sodium bisulfite
customer_reviews.text: I was shocked to find out such a good quality cat food as Natures variety,is now adding medadione sodium bisulfite to their food. I have found out from reliable sources that this is synthetic vitamin K, that even in small doses can be very harmful to our pets organs such as their lungs and kidneys. I will not be buying any pet food that contains this ingredient. Most high end pet foods add actual green leafy foods to supply vitamin K, but it is more expensive to do this, so the more inferior brands add the chemical instead.
customer_reviews.author: Fancy Nancy

customer_reviews.title: New formula causes vomiting
customer_reviews.text: My cats thrived on this food for a couple of years until the recent formula change. Now two of them are vomiting frequently and dealing with nausea and a third had to be moved onto wet food because she started having urinary crystals. I hate that they've changed such a great food and added ingredients which apparently to which a good portion of cats react negatively. Unfortunately I bought three bags at one time and now I'm stuck with two bags of cat food which my cats shouldn't eat!
customer_reviews.author: jkbtf

customer_reviews.title: New formula causes diarrhea for my cats. Changing brands!
customer_reviews.text: This used to be the only food my floof cat could eat without diarrhea. The new formula has changed this and she cannot handle it. I think it is the peas that cause upset stomach because when I pick them out of the instinct soft food she does better. There is no option to pick them out of the kibble however. So Nature's Variety has ruined a good thing for us and were searching for a new food again.
customer_reviews.author: RustingRooster

customer_reviews.title: Be aware!!!
customer_reviews.text: Be very careful. They have added peas as the 5 th ingredient which can cause kidney and bladder stones leading to costly surgery and even death in your pet. I will no longer be buying this.
customer_reviews.author: Daniel Kuzian

customer_reviews.title: no longer worth it
customer_reviews.text: They increased the price and gave it a so called "new look for 2017". The new look is less product for more money, this is a good product but way overpriced
customer_reviews.author: ITMan

customer_reviews.title: Didn't Expect This Result
customer_reviews.text: I've been purchasing the Instinct grain free wet cat food for a long time and would give it a 5-Star rating. Therefore, I decided to try their "quality" dry cat food. . .which was quite expensive for only 4.5 lbs. After opening the bag and setting some out for my cat, it was a no go! The cat sniffed it and promptly walked away. After trying for a week, I got the same result. Therefore, I put the dry food outside for a homeless cat I've been caring for. This cat sniffed it and promptly walked away. Even after several days, the cat would not eat it. Something is wrong with this dry cat food.
customer_reviews.author: L.M. in Texas

customer_reviews.title: Cause my cat to vomit. Avoid at all cost!
customer_reviews.text: Our two cats love the chicken flavor of this product, so we decided to change it up and have them try the rabbit flavor once. One of them vomited multiple times, and both of my cats refuse to eat any of it afterwards. Complete waste of money and judging by the other reviews, this is not a unique issue for my cats as it may be due to some new ingredients. We were going to donate the remaining bag but now it looks like we should throw it away.
customer_reviews.author: Robcar07

customer_reviews.title: Shiny Coat for Kitty
customer_reviews.text: I worked at a pet store for years and when it came down to choosing a cat food brand for my own cat it was such a hard decision! I spent years recommending different products to customers but it's totally different getting one yourself. I love that Nature's Variety is a high quality product that doesn't break the bank. It's highly palatable and I wanted something salmon to get all those fatty acids in my cats diet. She's a long hair and it's made her coat so healthy and soft. The bottom line is you can tell that real ingredients go into this food.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: May contain COCAINE!
customer_reviews.text: My cats gobble this stuff up like there is no tomorrow. I am convinced there has to be some sort of addictive illicit drug in it. If I try to feed them anything else the just look at me like I'm stupid and meow and/or stand on my face until I give them this. I am forced to keep buying this or risk an uprising of feline comrades. I recommend also buying the dash button with this and training your little devils to push it when they are hungry. Then they can just deal with the postman themselves and leave you out of it.
customer_reviews.author: drew

customer_reviews.title: My nearly 1-year-old kittens love this food
customer_reviews.text: My nearly 1-year-old kittens love this food. In fact, they love it so much, they broke into their food container and pigged out. The ingredients are top notch and these formerly-deathly-ill shelter kittens have grown very big and strong on Instinct. Their fur is glossy and shiny, their eyes are clear and bright, and no scratching, now that I have found a chicken-free formula. Yes, little ones can have allergies. It's great food; just be sure to order enough so that when they have shortages, which happened to us last time, you'll have enough to tide you over.
customer_reviews.author: awgoodkitty

customer_reviews.title: She said it wasn’t purrrrfect.
customer_reviews.text: My eight week old Bobtail didn’t like this food. The food looks like tiny chocolate chips. Smells kind of stinky, like catfood should.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. Grits

customer_reviews.title: Cats had diarrhea and bloody vomit
customer_reviews.text: I bought two different flavor of this food for my cats. They both had a bad reaction to the salmon bag after I transitioned them over from the rabbit flavor one. One of my cats had diarrhea while the other one had bloody vomit. I have had no issues with the food when I bought them in store but this bag I bought on amazon just seems to be giving both of my cats issues. I have contacted natures variety through their customer support line and they said they couldn’t do anything about it.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: New Formula Causes Allergies
customer_reviews.text: The old formula was great. I didn't have any trouble and my cats loved it. With the new formula, my kitty is always chewing at her skin and her fur started to fall out. As soon as I removed the food from her diet, skin issues cleared up and fur grew back in. I wish manufacturers would quit putting in all of the sugar (e.g. tapioca, peas). This is not biologically appropriate for cats. I'm sure the new formula is cheaper to manufacture but I wish manufacturers would leave the formula alone and let us pay a little more to continue with better quality.
customer_reviews.author: Megan

customer_reviews.title: Great for long hair cats
customer_reviews.text: My maine coon cat has been on this since he was a kitten. He is now a little over a year and switched to the adult bag. It keeps his coat soft and shiny. He has rarely had hairballs and has not grown bored of it.
customer_reviews.author: Christin Santa Maria

customer_reviews.title: Do NOT feed your cat!
customer_reviews.text: I was feeding this dry food to my male cat for 6 yrs with no issues. My cat suddenly became very ill and I rushed him to the vet. Unfortunately it was too late and my cat sadly passed away. The vet told me that it is very dangerous to feed cats, especially male cats, dry food. They become very dehydrated and develop kidney problems and kidney stones after years of eating dry food. My cat died from a kidney stone that cause a blockage of his urine. I don’t want this to happen to any one else’s cat. Switch to wet food!
customer_reviews.author: Rebecca Rozenberg

customer_reviews.title: PEAS!  And turkey, not all rabbit.
customer_reviews.text: The cat does not recommend this food. Why is there turkey in Rabbit flavor? and why PEAS?? Peas are horrible for pets. My cat is super sensitive to peas, and allergic to turkey. She will pick all the other kibble out of her dish and leave the "rabbit" in the bowl. We use a rotation diet, she knows when this is mixed in. (She says excuse you, there is turkey in her rabbit - She expected rabbit.) I agree with the cat, I don't recommend it.
customer_reviews.author: TJ

customer_reviews.title: Cat's love it, and has improved their health
customer_reviews.text: We have 3 cats, and when one began losing weight and was diagnosed with diabetes, we realized the need to switch to a grain free food. After much research, this food had the most protein and the fewest carbs of any dry food we could find. Our diabetic has returned to acting like herself (without insulin treatment) and has returned to a healthy weight, and all 3 have seen their coats become shinier and softer. And they all love it.
customer_reviews.author: F. ROBERTS

customer_reviews.title: Healthy AND the cats like it.
customer_reviews.text: I have a rotating menu for my cats, with a couple of different dry foods and multiple flavors and textures of wet foods that I mix for them. I have noticed that when this dry food is part of the mix, they are more likely to scarf the whole meal down instead of leaving some. Also, my daughter's cat came to visit, who was a very picky eater, and although she was turning her nose up at her own dry food (which is a quality grain-free brand), she did seem to enjoy this when I substituted it for her. I appreciate that this food does not include meat or bone meal from euthanized pets, too.
customer_reviews.author: kelleen thaxton

customer_reviews.title: The only cat food we buy(updated)
customer_reviews.text: Have tried everything and we have now found the best and will not change. Coat is shiny, stool not as stinky. We switch back and forth between chicken and salmon. I have tried giving her the freeze dried raw bits to add in, but she always regurgitates it. Update: Our cat has been on this food for about 6 months and has now developed diarrhea. Not sure of the reason, but we took her to the vet and he said there is nothing wrong with her, the food is just upsetting her stomach. Unfortunately, we had set it up as a subscribe item and we just got another huge bag of it. Will be switching.
customer_reviews.author: Robert

customer_reviews.title: Great value for healthy cat food
customer_reviews.text: My cats love this stuff better than wet food! Can't think of a higher endorsement. I like that the food is healthful for cat's diet and has options for chicken, rabbit, or duck protein sources and flavors. The only downside of the dry food is that the cats get dandruff and we add fish oils and little bits of wet food to compensate, as well as a Petmate drinking fountain. Value of the food is good for the money; lasts a long time and cats enjoy it, unlike wet foods that can be cold if refrigerated or dry out if they don't gobble it up first thing.
customer_reviews.author: Michael in Boston

customer_reviews.title: I love the Instinct food line but I have cats that ...
customer_reviews.text: I love the Instinct food line but I have cats that have some food allergies. I thought that this would work well for them since it is mainly a fish based flavour but they ended up reacting to the chicken fat that is used as a preservative. I switched them to the Limited Ingredient line and they do much better on that. This is not the food's fault but when I first started them on the recipe, the ingredient list did not show chicken fat as an ingredient so I don't know if the recipe was changed recently or not. They did just update the design of all of their bags and they look very nice.
customer_reviews.author: Loren

customer_reviews.title: Mixed feelings
customer_reviews.text: Our cat loved this cat food, both the dry and the canned. HOWEVER, she got diarrhea starting a couple of days after the first feeding. I kept giving her the food for a couple more days thinking her system would become accustomed to it; but the diarrhea continued. So I stopped the canned food, but kept up with the dry food. Diarrhea continued so I stopped that as well. Disappointed. It took 10 days after stopping both dry and canned, and her eating her previous brand, to get rid of the diarrhea.
customer_reviews.author: Sheila W.

customer_reviews.title: Keeps my Cat Healthy
customer_reviews.text: My cat devours this food. She had contracted food poisoning from Blue wet food when she was a kitten and refused to touch the stuff again(don't blame her), so I grabbed Instinct wet food and she loved it. I switched her gradually over to this dry food as well. She has been eating Instinct for over a year now and is doing great!! Her coat is shiny, she has a lot of energy, no health problems. This stuff is so expensive in stores so I was really happy Amazon had it for subscribe and save for less!
customer_reviews.author: Cassandra Manekas

customer_reviews.title: Second try,  cats get sick with this dried kind of food.
customer_reviews.text: I tried twice, this type of 100% protein for our two 5 year old cats. The first time they both did not tolerate the food. One became with upset stomach. I gave it a second chance; but this time both really got sick. With good intention, Favi
customer_reviews.author: Favi C

customer_reviews.title: Cat started throwing up
customer_reviews.text: My cat doesn't throw up normally, the first time she did she was 3 years old. I started feeding her Instinct Original 2 years ago, and she always eats it all. But about 6 months ago she started throwing up every day. There must have been some change in the recipe or my cat just developed an allergy, but I can't feed her this anymore.
customer_reviews.author: DawggieDawg

customer_reviews.title: My cats devour it
customer_reviews.text: I've tried a few different limited ingredient diets for my cats, and this is the one they love best and which doesn't upset their GI systems. Note that this isn't a true limited ingredient cat food, but it's more limited than most major brands, and the grain free aspect makes it easy on the cats. One of my cats gets really bad skin allergies with regular cat food, but not with this one.
customer_reviews.author: Darren

customer_reviews.title: All I'll buy my cat
customer_reviews.text: Pricy but only for I'll get for my cat. After trying many different ones--between health issues, LOTS of research and the vet suggestions--this is the only one I will get my cat. She only likes the chicken flavor but it's healthy and gives her the perfect amount of nutrients. We had tried blue Buffalo and other well-known brands but she either did not like them or would get intestinal issues due to too much protein. This seems to give her everything she needs without upsetting her stomach. I do also have cat grass for her though.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Cat does not like recent formula change
customer_reviews.text: I was on the autoship program for this product, but our cat stopped eating it, once we started a new bag. I contacted the manufacturer and got this response: We did recently update the formulas on some of our recipes and the chicken was one of them so it may be that you got a bag of the older version and then one of the newer version. We have a 100% guarantee on all of our products so if you reach out to amazon they should be able to just refund your account.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: ... had been trying to move our cats to a better quality cat food for a while now
customer_reviews.text: We had been trying to move our cats to a better quality cat food for a while now. After some failures, and some more research, we tried to give Instinct (duck) a try. First, we tried the version with the freeze-dried kibble in it, but they wouldn't eat the kibble, so we opted for this version. Well, we have a winner!
customer_reviews.author: Donna

customer_reviews.title: My cats weren’t a fan
customer_reviews.text: Bought this by accident instead of the one with the freeze dried raw chicken. I have two savannah cats who eat raw meat and sometimes dry food. Without the freeze dried chicken, they wanted no parts of it.
customer_reviews.author: CW

customer_reviews.title: Good for cats with digestive problems.
customer_reviews.text: My cats have been eating this brand for years. I have a Maine Coon who has a very delicate digestive system and it took me months to find a food that he could tolerate. Only negative is the price.
customer_reviews.author: D. Henry

customer_reviews.title: Great, clean product for cats.
customer_reviews.text: I'm not a cat and my cat can't give me a review, but she eats it. Per the ingredients list, I felt like this was a great option for my cat. She never had any issues with it and liked this flavor. I've since stopped buying it due to the high price point. It is worth it for sure for the product you get, but sadly I switched to a different brand, also great quality, but bounds cheaper. Would highly recommend this product though.
customer_reviews.author: KWalker17

customer_reviews.title: Way too expensive.. $18 yeah right
customer_reviews.text: This was when I bought it $4.95 for a 2.2 bag, and my cat liked it. Now its $12.99! and I don't like that. Now its $17.99! you would have to be insane to pay $8 for a pound of anything. Guess my cat will be eating more boneless chicken breast at $2-3 lb or I can buy 2 or 3 whole chickens already cooked for that price or a 20lb bag of leg quarters. So if you want your cat to have good quality protein its a LOT cheaper to just buy a chicken and cook it for your cat. Freeze the leftovers.
customer_reviews.author: grafdog

customer_reviews.title: Poor quality control
customer_reviews.text: Returned the item due to kibble pieces being deformed and way too large for cats. I was scared about quality since so much of the bag was deformed. I would buy in store, though I’m apprehensive to do that now too.
customer_reviews.author: PF

customer_reviews.title: Good Quality
customer_reviews.text: We have been feeding this to our ferrets for almost a year now and they love it! Their coats have gotten more thick and their stool stays perfectly normal. The only complaint I have: WHY did they add peas to the recipe?! We might eventually have to switch because peas are terrible for ferrets, which makes us so sad. If you are feeding to ONLY a cat, however, I would recommend!
customer_reviews.author: Daniel

customer_reviews.title: Great taste, great product.
customer_reviews.text: The only dry cat food that so found to be free of any poultry products! I have a cat allergic to any type of poultry. Tired of reading the small print on cans and packages. Comes with great taste, she eats it all up.
customer_reviews.author: Dee

customer_reviews.title: High Protein Good - But Not for Older Male Cats
customer_reviews.text: Great food, but not for older male cats. It can cause and exacerbate kidney failure due to the high protein content. I learned the hard way that I should have spoken to my vet before switching my cats over to this.
customer_reviews.author: THAGONZ

customer_reviews.title: Another Wrong Choice
customer_reviews.text: Not one of my three cats will touch this "food". They sniff it and look at me like they are being punished for something. To be a high end brand, it's a colossal failure.
customer_reviews.author: Caki

customer_reviews.title: Higher protein kibble that cats love.
customer_reviews.text: Mostly we feed our cat wet pate cat food on the recommendation of our vet. She said any kibble we use should be higher in protein as cats are carnivores and the fewer carbs and additives in kibbles, the better for the cat. This had a higher protein than many dry cat food without being as expensive as some, though people on a budge probably couldn't afford it.
customer_reviews.author: Karen K

customer_reviews.title: but not at all happy with the new sizing on the packages
customer_reviews.text: My cats thrive on this, but not at all happy with the new sizing on the packages. I've used it for several years and it always came in the 12.1 lb size and now I can only find the 11 lbs size for the same price. Will buy it till I can find something a bit more affordable for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Patricia Van Tine

customer_reviews.title: Impossible packaging
customer_reviews.text: The cat food is fine, and has been for years, but the bag has become impossible. The zip closure is several inches down on one side only and it is impossible for me for properly close it. I have trimmed the top and folded it over, but after testing to see that it is sealed, I come back for the next meal and it is not. That lets the food get stale very quickly. I emailed this complaint to the manufacturer many months ago and received a coupon for another bag (!) but no indication of reviewing the design. I will not buy this again.
customer_reviews.author: Carol E.

customer_reviews.title: Never experienced this before!
customer_reviews.text: I bought the rabbit and the chicken and have never had this problem before! In BOTH cases the first 1/2 of the bag, the nuggets were rock hard to the point that my cat could not eat them! :-( I am very disappointed as my cat really liked this product! I am not sure what happened, but I will have to find a new brand I guess.....
customer_reviews.author: Leslie A Schramm

customer_reviews.title: Favorite Dry for our 7 Cats
customer_reviews.text: Contains No grains or refined carbs, has human grade ingredients, is one of the best dry foods out there and our cats love it. We feed it as a bedtime snack....Cats do not get dry food in nature and should never have a dry food diet alone, unless we want to create kidney issues for them.
customer_reviews.author: Snow Wise

customer_reviews.title: My cats enjoyed it
customer_reviews.text: We have an older cat that tends to vomit up his food a lot. The vet feels that he is protein sensitive and recommended duck or rabbit so I purchased this food and both cats enjoyed it but the vomiting resumed after a few weeks on it so I switched them to a sensitive stomach formula that seems to be working better for him. However, they both really enjoyed this one and I can’t fault it for his food sensitivity.
customer_reviews.author: short-n-sweet

customer_reviews.title: This cat food is amazing
customer_reviews.text: First off it's grain free which is great and it has a nice strong smell for the cats. If you did not know, cats will only consume food they can smell and that smells good to them. My cat loves this feed and I appreciate the fact that it's well priced for the quality i'm getting. Another good thing to note is that it includes nutrition facts. Cat's should only consume about 150 calories a day especially if they are not very active so a bad of food like this goes a long way.
customer_reviews.author: Justin

customer_reviews.title: Good quality food
customer_reviews.text: I got my kittens when they were only a week old and bottle fed them. I wanted only the best food so started with Purina One, then switched to Origen, but it is so expensive. Found this with similar ingredients and it was 100% accepted. They have been on this for about 2 years, each weigh about 13 pounds, have beautiful shiny coats and love to play. They each get 1/3 cup a day and a wet food in morning.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: My cat loves it
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this food. I bought it because it is supposed to be healthier for cats because it is grain-free. Cats are not supposed to eat grain and many supermarket brands contains grains. My cat is in love with this food and whenever I tried to change it, so he can try something else, he was not happy with my decision! We will stick with this food then :)
customer_reviews.author: Nina Segura

customer_reviews.title: Watch for allergic reactions
customer_reviews.text: My cat never really liked this food but I stuck with it because I thought it was good quality food. Then a month ago, I noticed he started to get very soft stools. The vet put him on antibiotics for a week. Got better but then worse again when he was done with the meds. It got so bad that he was pooping bloody liquid stools. He doesn’t go outside so it must have been the food. The vet recommended switching and he was instantly better. I think he developed an allergic reaction to something in this food. Would not recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Greyathena

customer_reviews.title: Great quality food
customer_reviews.text: My cat has serious allergies and it's VERY difficult to find cat food that does not contain ingredients he is allergic to. (potatoes, flaxseed, rice, beef or pork especially) Instinct is the only brand I have found that is under $50 for a 12 pound bag. Instinct also is a very good quality food with real, wholesome ingredients. No by-products which is great! We have two cats and one bag lasts us about a month and a half. Their coat is silky and they love their food.
customer_reviews.author: sjones6321

customer_reviews.title: Doesn't work anymore
customer_reviews.text: Used to love, but I am wondering if they changed some ingredients because my girl now throws it up after eating. Had to find a new option.
customer_reviews.author: skye mach

customer_reviews.title: Quality Control
customer_reviews.text: I have been getting Instinct Dry Cat food for years. The last bag I received was so crumbly that I had to throw most of it away. I was looking into purchasing a different brand when the next bag arrived. It was back to the quality I expected. I would like to receive a replacement 11# bag for the bad bag and request that the company be more diligent in their quality control!
customer_reviews.author: Dream Weaver

customer_reviews.title: The quality is always great and consistent!
customer_reviews.text: I finally found a grain free dry food that my cat loves! The kibble has the perfect size for even small cats mouths. I free feed her and her body weight has stayed just where it should be. Her long hair coat looks wonderful and she doesn't throw up like she used to do with the other dry food I bought. I've been buying this food for almost 2 years and I have no plans to try anything else.
customer_reviews.author: Lea Ann Lewis

customer_reviews.title: Quality Food
customer_reviews.text: I had some experience with Instinct because I purchased beef canned for my cat with allergies so when I got a new kitten I was looking for a good quality for all life stages. I decided to try this one and the vet tech from whom I adopted the kitten said she believed it was a good quality food. Kitten is satisfied and growing nicely with a beautiful shiny coat..
customer_reviews.author: K-Lady

customer_reviews.title: Ferret is thriving on this brand
customer_reviews.text: Rescued a ferret about 6 months ago, he was malnourished from the Marshall food and his poop was very runny. Switched to Instinct immediately, it was recommended to me from a long time ferret owner. He has gained weight, has more energy, his fur looks amazing, he is just all around a new ferret. Im sure all the new love and attention is also a big contributor! Normally buy the chicken flavor, but just purchased the duck flavor and hoping he will love it as well!
customer_reviews.author: Shannon

customer_reviews.title: Good food makes good poop
customer_reviews.text: The cat is healthy. Her coat and nails and teeth are all good. She’s been eating this for over two years now. She is 5. Her poop is firm and doesn’t make you want to puke. The pet sitter told me it’s the healthiest poop she’s seen. Proud Mama here.
customer_reviews.author: DeeLou

customer_reviews.title: Not for my cat
customer_reviews.text: Wanted to try a low carb kibble for my diabetic cat and this stood out. Unfortunately, while I only added a teaspoon to his regular kibble, he has had loose stool and is defecating more frequently. It also had a stink to it. Don't get me wrong, poop doesn't smell great, but while trying to switch it was awful. I stopped giving it to him and he has returned to normal. I'm sure this is great food, just not for my cat.
customer_reviews.author: Jessica

customer_reviews.title: Picky eater likes it, no digestive issues
customer_reviews.text: My picky eater likes it. It is grain free. She's not having the digestive issues and vomiting like she was on another brand. She gets mostly a canned, grain free food, another brand, she didn't like this brand of canned for some reason or another. She's happy, I'm happy!
customer_reviews.author: 4Horses

customer_reviews.title: The old puppers have more energy and better mobility since switching to this food and better poops
customer_reviews.text: I have 5 small dogs. 1 red miniature Pinscher, 4 years old. 2 chiweenies, 3 years old. 1 Pomeranian, 14 years old. 1 Chihuahua, 15 years old. The old puppers have more energy and better mobility since switching to this food and better poops, no diarrhea. They all love this so much that they picked around the "old" kibble that was mixed in for transitioning to new food.
customer_reviews.author: hilde wunderbar

customer_reviews.title: Great food.
customer_reviews.text: Switching to rabbit from chicken and turkey has helped our cats with stomach and allergy issues. They all love it. Great price on Amazon with subscribe and save.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Cats don't like it
customer_reviews.text: I have 3 non finicky cats. They discontinued their grain free food so I tried this. Put just this in a tiny plate for them to try. 2 days later still there. There is something not right about this food. If 3 different breeds of cat won't go near it that says it all. Now I have a very expensive bag of food they won't eat.
customer_reviews.author: ladyesmiles

customer_reviews.title: My Percy loves it!
customer_reviews.text: I have used this product for several years. My cat has less "throw-ups" and can go longer between meals because the food has no fillers. I top his food off with a couple of crumbled Raw Boost Mixers and he's happy as a clam.
customer_reviews.author: Susan A. Elder

customer_reviews.title: Great product
customer_reviews.text: I thought after the research I did that the cats would go for it. No, they didn't like this, so I continue to search, I have more coming tomorrow so hopefully, they will eat the right kind of kibble, not eating this. A cat who adopted me lives on the patio and two are inside and he is not wild about it either. Sigh
customer_reviews.author: Shirley M.

customer_reviews.title: My cat loves this kibble more than wet food
customer_reviews.text: It's weird. Anyway, my other cats enjoy this food as well. It makes one of them very shiny compared to other foods. We always get this type and this flavor because they enjoy it and it keeps them happy. If we get the one with little freeze dried pieces they end up only eating those pieces and they get salty about eating the kibble. They also hate the rabbit flavor and wont touch it.
customer_reviews.author: HiiiMouse

customer_reviews.title: Grain Free
customer_reviews.text: Love that it is grain free and small like kibble. Bought this as a treat for my cats since the treats came in only small amounts. They love it and never realized it was food instead of treats.
customer_reviews.author: Toni L

customer_reviews.title: would recommend!
customer_reviews.text: my cat loves this food! she’s very happy and energetic. i’m pretty sure her coat has gotten a lot softer and shinier since starting her on this food. since cats can not be vegan i recommend feeding them salmon/fish over beef or any other animal. it’s better for the environment, your cats health and you are helping to not endorse large scale factory farming (animal cruelty). thank you!
customer_reviews.author: Grace J

customer_reviews.title: My kitty loves this food!
customer_reviews.text: I tried this once because it was on a store special. My kitty just loved it so I have continued to buy it for him. I feel it is very good for him with all the ingredients listed. Thank you for carrying this great brand of cat food!
customer_reviews.author: Leelee Gerlach

customer_reviews.title: bag slit inside larger box
customer_reviews.text: The cat good bag has a large slit in the front. Much of the food had spilled out into the outer box and then spilled out openings in the box due to poor handling. The Prime driver pointed out the problem and suggested I contact you. I'm not comfortable feeding my cats this mixture.
customer_reviews.author: katherine lancaster

customer_reviews.title: Mistakenly ordered the chicken when I intended to purchase the ...
customer_reviews.text: Mistakenly ordered the chicken when I intended to purchase the duck. Makes a big difference with my cat; he rarely eats it—and he doesn’t come across as finicky but he can certainly do without this one. Duck is on the way. I still think the product is great-ingredients seem healthier than many.
customer_reviews.author: LG

customer_reviews.title: Cats love this stuff
customer_reviews.text: Really pleased with the results in feeding this cat food. Both my long and shorthaired cats look great, with shiny healthy hair. Follow the feeding instructions because feeding too much will put on weight. Litterbox is a breeze to clean up too. Low odor and not much waste to scoop!! Big PLUS!
customer_reviews.author: Ann L.

customer_reviews.title: Caused my cat to vomit.
customer_reviews.text: My cat ate this food for a couple months and then in January started vomiting it up almost daily. I started brushing him daily, giving him LAX for hairballs, made sure there was nothing around he could chew on, but he kept vomiting. I finally stopped feeding this dry food and the vomiting stopped.
customer_reviews.author: Sherry G

customer_reviews.title: Cats love this!
customer_reviews.text: All of our cats adore Instinct to the point one of them actually rips the bag open if I accidentally forget to shut the pantry door. The ingredient list is ultra high quality as well which leaves me as happy as my cats!
customer_reviews.author: Apollo

customer_reviews.title: 17 pound kitty to a 12 pound kitty
customer_reviews.text: Quality food. Smells really good. My cat loves it! And surprisingly this food has helped my cat loose 5 pounds! I have tried wet food only diet, hills science perfection weight wet food and blue buffalo weight control food. None of them worked. But this food has been helping my kitty loose weight and meanwhile making sure that he is energetic. (My cat is a 3 year old male Persian who doesn’t play much, and I’ve been giving him an eighth cup a day.)
customer_reviews.author: Yiyu

customer_reviews.title: Complete daily offering
customer_reviews.text: We own a Maine Coon Cat. He is large but isn’t a cat who overheats. We feed him Instinct exclusively. He loves it and I feel free to leave it on the floor until it is all gone. Instinct is a complete diet so I know I only have to provide 24/7 water to keep him satisfied.
customer_reviews.author: KT

customer_reviews.title: The Best for my cats.
customer_reviews.text: It is the best for a beautiful coat. Now if you've got a cat leaning towards to being over weight, then you might want to check their other products.
customer_reviews.author: PurlyGates

customer_reviews.title: We tried a variety of foods, this wasn't wasn't their favorite
customer_reviews.text: My cats stopped eating Blue Buffalo in June 2018 so we had to try a bunch of different foods to see what they would eat. My cats ate this, but they didn't greedily devour it. Maybe your cats are different.
customer_reviews.author: electricquad

customer_reviews.title: Kitty is picky and she likes this food
customer_reviews.text: I have a kitty that is a little OCD. She hates anything new. I wanted to improve her nutrition and tried a raw food, no luck. She rejected it out right. This has some raw dehydrated food coats the kibble. I mixed it with her old food and she went right for the new kibble. too. Yeah.
customer_reviews.author: judy b

customer_reviews.title: My ferrets love it!
customer_reviews.text: As a ferret owner I know that it's important to feed them a proper diet. Many of the ferret foods on the market are full of trash , but this brand of cat food is amazing. The ingredient quality is superb , the only issue is the peas in the food that lead to bladder stone formation. The product arrived on time and as described.
customer_reviews.author: Timmer Peters

customer_reviews.title: caused diarrhea to cat
customer_reviews.text: This cat food caused diarrhea to my cat. It is very weird because I was slowly switching the cat food, and only mixed in about 10% of the new cat food and yet it still caused diarrhea. Not sure if there's a ingredient that my cat is sensitive to or if I got a bag from a bad batch. (FYI I was switching from Pro Plan to this, and now is planning on switching to Nulo...)
customer_reviews.author: Haoda Ma

customer_reviews.title: Worked for my food allergy kitty
customer_reviews.text: My cat had severe ear infections and after three vets, sleepless nights, and a lot of crying, a good vet had me put him on Royal Cain pea and rabbit to see if a food allergy was the root cause. It was. Royal Cain is expensive and kitty started having dandruff issues. I tried this food and he is dandruff free AND his ears are still clear.
customer_reviews.author: jennifer W.

customer_reviews.title: helped our cat with digestive problems
customer_reviews.text: AWESOME CAT FOOD! NO GRAIN AND IT ALSO HAS RAW FOOD IN IT! This really helped our cat with digestive problems. They are small ball like objects so if your cat is picky about the shapes or feel a certain way then you will have to do a gradual switching out. Our cat loves this so much she thinks its a treat!!
customer_reviews.author: AaronDrTop Contributor: Coloring

customer_reviews.title: Cat loves this food he makes out with the box.
customer_reviews.text: Cat makes out with the box when it arrives. He loves this brand. His coat always looks great, and if you have a picky eater...try this one. Was a must to have grain free for him and this fits the bill with his allergies.
customer_reviews.author: Thairaven1

customer_reviews.title: Healthy food, Tabby's Love!
customer_reviews.text: Great Ingredients. Our two Tabby boys, Lex & Luthor, gobble up😻😻! (Although, they aren't too picky). Poos can be kinda smelly though.😷 I clean out their litter box 3-4 times a day to alleviate that problem. 👍 Healthy food, they love which makes Momma Happy! 🙂
customer_reviews.author: Gina 🙂

customer_reviews.title: My cats fur is so silky now! :)
customer_reviews.text: My cat's fur is soooo shiny and soft! He was having health problems so I chose to change his cat food to something with out grains and he has been so much better off for it. It does have a fishy smell but he eats it up and licks his chops so well worth it! I would give it a 10 star if I could!
customer_reviews.author: Astrid

customer_reviews.title: Very high quality ingredients
customer_reviews.text: This is the only food I order for my cats. It has very high quality ingredients and my cats always eat it without issue.
customer_reviews.author: Michelle S.

customer_reviews.title: Well-tolerated by cats with bad digestion
customer_reviews.text: On the plus side, this is the food my female cat throws up least often (usually only when she overeats, as compared to anything with corn in it which gets on the floor 20 minutes later). Her less picky brother is fine with it, too. They're both healthy, muscular and thin (desired look for Siamese) so it's not going to make your cat fat, as well as fairly active. On the minus side, this is very expensive. My cats are eating way better quality food than I am.
customer_reviews.author: Bobby

customer_reviews.title: Split decision.
customer_reviews.text: I picked this up because we were having a hard time getting our regular brand due to people over shopping ! It has small round pellets.The bag states no by products.It has a very strong fish smell so if your cat likes that you may like this food for them.
customer_reviews.author: anthony

customer_reviews.title: Not sure it makes him a bobcat like the label but it is good quality food
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this stuff. They must put cat version of crack in it. Not sure it makes him a bobcat like the label but it is good quality food. He has never turned it down or gotten tired of it like other foods. Recommended.
customer_reviews.author: Bovineplane

customer_reviews.title: Horrible, made my cat omitting for 3 days
customer_reviews.text: It is just that bad... I have no idea and have to waste this ten pound expensive food... SAD
customer_reviews.author: Colin

customer_reviews.title: Salivating For Salmon
customer_reviews.text: My cat went absolutely bananas at the smell of this bag of food! The second I took it out of the box she was flipping off walls and chirping her excitement. I only exclusively buy Nature’s Variety food products (both wet and dry) because they are the number one cat food brand out there and I feel confident about what I’m feeding to my precious baby. She loves to eat it and I love the piece of mind it gives me. It is a bit on the pricey side but, it’s definitely worth it!
customer_reviews.author: Ani M.

customer_reviews.title: Wonderful formula!
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves this food. She’s happier and healthier than ever before, even though I fed her another grain free food.
customer_reviews.author: BV

customer_reviews.title: Bag size decreased over a pound, but same price. Thumbs down.
customer_reviews.text: The bag redesign is really just an attempt to distract from the fact they decreased the bag from 12.1 lbs to 11 lbs, but kept the same price. Disappointed in this company.
customer_reviews.author: Sarah K Williams

customer_reviews.title: I feed this food to my borderline diabetic cat because ...
customer_reviews.text: I feed this food to my borderline diabetic cat because it's high protein content and he loves it more than he likes his wet food.
customer_reviews.author: drawingthoughts

customer_reviews.title: The good stuff!!
customer_reviews.text: I seriously think this is a great choice for my cat. She's taking a while to warm up to this healthy brand of food. But as she's getting older. I heard this was the brand to put her on. It seems like she maybe finally liking it. I think it smells good and fresh and say what's there not to like. If I was a cat I would dig it.
customer_reviews.author: Stephanie Kenyon

customer_reviews.title: The cats give it two paws up rating.
customer_reviews.text: My cats love this food even better than the Iams natural I had been feeding them. This is a little more expensive for the amount of food, but my “babies” are 15 yrs old and are worth the cost if it keeps them healthy and happy.
customer_reviews.author: Dyna309

customer_reviews.title: 😻Kitty Approved😻
customer_reviews.text: My little Furball loves his cat food. He has been eating it for 3 years now. Never tired of it. It’s grain free and has healthy ingredients. What more can you ask for? Your kitty may like it too!😻
customer_reviews.author: ZombeeUnicorn🦄

customer_reviews.title: Dry raw cat food that keeps my cats happy and healthy
customer_reviews.text: Great flavorful dry raw cat food! I supplement this dry food with the instinct wet cat food .. works great!
customer_reviews.author: David Isbell

customer_reviews.title: My three cats won't eat this Instinct food, dry or canned.
customer_reviews.text: I DISLIKE that I cannot CANCEL my Subscribe & Save Subscription! I have gone in circles at every part of this program, finding there are "NO BUTTONS" for editing or cancelling. I caution anyone to sign up for this S&S. Don't do it. It's another trip to hell.
customer_reviews.author: Kathryn Busby

customer_reviews.title: Happy and healthy cats
customer_reviews.text: I feel good about this product and the cats don't complain. Eagerly wait for it. I have one kitten and one 9 year old. They are very healthy.
customer_reviews.author: Awakening Peacefully

customer_reviews.title: Stinks to high heaven & cat doesn’t like 2nd bag
customer_reviews.text: I’ve got mixed emotions on this cat food. At first my cat couldn’t get enough. Now, he hardly eats any. Not to mention his cardiologist said he wasn’t sold on the “grain free fad”...in his words.
customer_reviews.author: Mary R.K.

customer_reviews.title: Bengal loves it!
customer_reviews.text: My Bengal girl absolutely loves this and it's really good quality food for the price worth every penny great ingredients!
customer_reviews.author: megan zins

product_meta.title: Instinct Original Grain Free Recipe Natural Dry Cat Food
product_meta.description: Flavor Name:Rabbit| Size:10 lb. BagHigh protein, grain free recipes guided by our belief in raw, each recipe starts with responsibly sourced real meat and is made with 70%+ real animal ingredients & nutritious oils, 30% vegetables, fruits and other wholesome ingredients. We put the pure, real nutrition of raw on every piece of Instinct Original by tumbling our kibble with crushed, freeze dried raw – raising the bar in nutrition and taste. Instinct Original is a best selling cat food made with guaranteed levels of live, natural probiotics, natural omegas and antioxidants for digestive health, healthy skin & coat, and immune health. This grain free, gluten free cat food is made without grain, potato, corn, wheat, soy, by product meal, artificial colors or preservatives - ingredients known to trigger food sensitivity. Instinct Original grain free cat food is complete and balanced nutrition for all cats, kittens, adult and senior, and is available in a variety of natural dry cat food recipes: Cage-Free Chicken, Cage-Free Duck, Farm-Raised Rabbit, Wild-Caught Salmon. Made in the USA with the finest ingredients from around the world and available in dry cat food and canned cat food pate. Satisfaction guaranteed. Questions? Call Instinct at 888-519-7387.
feature_bullets: GRAIN FREE CAT FOOD WITH FARM RAISED RABBIT: Instinct Original dry cat food is made with 80% real animal ingredients and nutritious oils, 20% vegetables, fruits and other wholesome ingredients. Responsibly sourced farm raised rabbit is the #1 ingredient.

NATURAL CAT FOOD: Instinct Original dry cat food is high protein cat food made with probiotics to support healthy digestion and omegas for skin & coat. Made without grain, potato, corn, wheat, soy, by-product meals, artificial colors or preservatives.

THE FIRST RAW COATED KIBBLE: Our grain free cat food offers balanced nutrition for all cats, including indoor & kittens. Each piece of kibble is coated in freeze dried raw for nutrition & taste. Delicious, healthy flavor that even picky kitties will love.

POWER OF RAW INGREDIENTS: Our cat food is made with the pure, real nutrition of raw. Raw is natural, made from real meat & whole food ingredients, protein packed & minimally processed. Made in the USA with the finest ingredients from around the world.

INSTINCT, THE RAW BRAND: We craft dry & wet cat food from real ingredients. Compare Instinct to Blue Buffalo, Fancy Feast, Hills Science Diet, Royal Canin, Rachel Ray, Natural Balance, Merrick, Purina One, Friskies, Wellness, Iams, Purina Beyond & Weruva.
